{
  "stem": "21786.4",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But half a year after we left there-- filmed there a film, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] which was called 'Hitler gibt der Juden eine Stadt,' Hitler is giving the Jews a city.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And the whole Theresienstadt, all Theresien was painted and everything was arranged there.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I mean, there was a coffee shop and a restaurant, and there were orchestras playing, and the children were thanking to the SS men for enabling them doing this and that.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And while we were still in Theresien, it was obvious that one is preparing something like this.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Yet every week, a transport was leaving.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And with every transport, as we were taken out from this daily transport, we automatically fell into the transport, meaning Eva and I, and our parents, who came later then.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But we were specifically in every transport.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "We were always put out on some reason, which was arranged at the council of elders.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And finally, we were called by Edelstein [INAUDIBLE] and who told us, kids, you both are very likable.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "I can understand that it will sound to you very absurd.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "But I cannot protect you.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "We cannot protect you as bridegroom and bride.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "You have to get married.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we said, so we'll get married.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So the next-- I think the next-- the day after this, two days later, we were married.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were married in a room which the Germans specifically left for that.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "One has to realize that families did not live-- live together.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Men lived with men, women lived with women, and similar.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And the contact was forbidden, yet [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] this was a ghetto.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Everything was possible in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the Germans, they agreed.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "People even get-- can get married.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
